<subSubSection id="88DE6550FFB5FFDA0F9CBC40C0FCFC5E" pageId="23" pageNumber="297" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C07B36DBFFB5FFDA0F9CBC40C0FCFC5E" blockId="23.[160,1156,849,1013]" pageId="23" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="F2B0EAC9FFB5FFDA0F9CBC40C3E0FCC2" bold="true" box="[160,421,849,873]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="297">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Antenna serrate, antennomeres progressively narrower towards apex; posterior corners of pronotum acute; elytron elliptic. Dorsal colour pattern overall black, with a longitudinal pale yellow stripe on elytra. The male flash pattern of this species has been recorded as a repeat of five short, evenly spaced flashes (emitted within two seconds). Female flash pattern is unknown.
</paragraph>
